";}}}i:35509;O:29:"Illuminate\\Support\\Collection":1:{s:8:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'items";a:1:{i:0;a:4:{s:4:"type";s:16:"constructor_base";s:2:"id";s:5:"35510";s:4:"sort";s:3:"500";s:4:"text";s:4925:"<p>COVID-19 (Corona Virus Disease 2019) is&nbsp;an&nbsp;acute respiratory disease caused by&nbsp;SARS-CoV-2 virus (Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Coronavirus&nbsp;2).</p>
<p>SARS-CoV-2&nbsp;is one of&nbsp;betacoronaviruses&nbsp;&mdash; a&nbsp;genus, which representatives for the third time in&nbsp;the 21<sup>st</sup> century have crossed the interspecies barrier (the infection came from bats) and have caused acute respiratory disorders in&nbsp;humans (atypical pneumonia caused by&nbsp;SARS-CoV-1 in&nbsp;2002, middle east respiratory syndrome caused by&nbsp;MERS-CoV in&nbsp;2012, and now COVID-19 caused by&nbsp;SARS-CoV-2). </p>
<p>The main transmission modes of&nbsp;SARS-CoV-2 are airborne and contact. The virus can survive in&nbsp;the air during 3&nbsp;hours and on&nbsp;most of&nbsp;the surfaces&nbsp;&mdash; up&nbsp;to&nbsp;72&nbsp;hours. </p>
<p>The disease COVID-19&nbsp;is highly contagious and characterized by&nbsp;the long period of&nbsp;incubation (from 2&nbsp;to&nbsp;14&nbsp;days, in&nbsp;average&nbsp;&mdash; 5&nbsp;days), 25-30% of&nbsp;the infected people do&nbsp;not have any symptoms but&nbsp;15% of&nbsp;them develop severe symptoms like viral pneumonia that may lead to&nbsp;death. The risk group includes elderly people and those suffering from chronic conditions like asthma, diabetes mellitus, cardiovascular diseases, chronic respiratory conditions, immune system disorders as&nbsp;well as&nbsp;pregnant women.</p>
<p>Pregnancy as&nbsp;a&nbsp;risk factor is&nbsp;explained by&nbsp;general changes in&nbsp;the immune system, heavier load on&nbsp;all body systems and impossibility to&nbsp;take antiviral drugs during this period (practically all antiviral medications are teratogenic, i.e. cause birth defects). </p>
<p>So&nbsp;far, we&nbsp;do&nbsp;not have enough data of&nbsp;COVID-19-related risks for pregnant women. Among pregnant patients infected with SARS-CoV-1, the mortality rate was&nbsp;25% and among those with МERS-CoV&nbsp;&mdash; 23%. There are no&nbsp;published data on&nbsp;patients with COVID-19 in&nbsp;the first trimester of&nbsp;pregnancy, 48&nbsp;cases described in&nbsp;the literature (7&nbsp;publications) refer to&nbsp;the second and third trimesters. Most of&nbsp;authors insist on&nbsp;the fact the virus does not cross the placenta barrier, does not penetrate into breast milk and the newborns with COVID-19 were infected by&nbsp;airborne transmission after the childbirth though the virus can be&nbsp;also found in&nbsp;the fecal masses and the fecal-oral route was also possible during the childbirth. At&nbsp;the same time, the mass media informed of&nbsp;several cases of&nbsp;vertical transmission of&nbsp;COVID-19 to&nbsp;newborns (from a&nbsp;mother to&nbsp;a&nbsp;fetus through placenta), which caused concern.</p>
<p>In&nbsp;spite of&nbsp;the fact that there are no&nbsp;data on&nbsp;the effect of&nbsp;COVID-19&nbsp;on conception and the first trimester of&nbsp;pregnancy, still there is&nbsp;an&nbsp;ongoing discussion of&nbsp;how the virus penetrates into a&nbsp;host cell. The human angiotensin-converting enzyme&nbsp;2 (ACE2) protein is&nbsp;considered to&nbsp;be&nbsp;the point of&nbsp;entry for the SARS-CoV-2 virus into human cells. ACE2 protein is&nbsp;widely represented in&nbsp;the cells of&nbsp;the human vessels, the heart, the kidneys, the intestines, the fat tissue and the central neural system. Research findings show that ACE2 can be&nbsp;found in&nbsp;male seminal glands, which causes alert that the virus can also be&nbsp;sexually transmitted. Besides, the increased number of&nbsp;ACE2 was found in&nbsp;the ovaries and its amount is&nbsp;regulated by&nbsp;hormones. In&nbsp;the uterine lining of&nbsp;reproductive age women the ACE2 protein is&nbsp;increased during the second (secretory) phase of&nbsp;the menstrual cycle. The existing data confirms that ACE2 protein is&nbsp;active in&nbsp;the placenta tissue and amniotic fluid. There has been a&nbsp;message about finding the virus in&nbsp;breast milk. So, by&nbsp;now we&nbsp;cannot accurately estimate the risks of&nbsp;SARS-CoV-2&rsquo;s effect on&nbsp;conception, implantation, embryo development and pregnancy in&nbsp;the first trimester.</p>
<p>The data mentioned above have determined the opinion of&nbsp;the specialists in&nbsp;human reproduction in&nbsp;the whole world (ESHRE on&nbsp;March&nbsp;14, ASRM on&nbsp;March&nbsp;17, ICMART on&nbsp;March&nbsp;28, RAHR on&nbsp;April 2&nbsp;and FIGO on&nbsp;April&nbsp;4) of&nbsp;the necessity to&nbsp;stop ART procedures for the period of&nbsp;the COVID-19&nbsp;pandemic. The most reliable marker of&nbsp;a&nbsp;possibility of&nbsp;safe pregnancy after the pandemic may be&nbsp;finding antibodies but no&nbsp;viral load in&nbsp;the patients entering the IVF cycle (i.e. health condition and PCR test must indicate the absence of&nbsp;virus and the antibody mediated immunity will protect both mother and baby).</p>";}}}i:66997;O:29:"Illuminate\\Support\\Collection":1:{s:8:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'items";a:1:{i:0;a:4:{s:4:"type";s:16:"constructor_base";s:2:"id";s:5:"66999";s:4:"sort";s:3:"500";s:4:"text";s:1752:"В мае МЦРМ принял участие во II Конгрессе Ассоциации репродуктивной медицины Узбекистана.<br />
<br />
Заведующая отделением ВРТ Эльвира Валентиновна Исакова выступила с докладом «Теория и практика поддержки лютеиновой фазы цикла в программах ВРТ». Его назвали лучшим из всех прослушанных на конгрессе.<br />
<br />
А гендиректор МЦРМ, профессор Владислав Станиславович Корсак получил награду «За выдающийся вклад в развитие репродуктивной медицины Узбекистана».<br />
<br />
Волнующим событием стало посещение клиники «Доктор Шахноза Файз ЭКО». Директор Шахноза Файзуллаевна Баходырова отметила большой вклад сотрудников МЦРМ в создание ВРТ в Узбекистане. Благодаря многолетнему сотрудничеству с МЦРМ у пациентов клиники на день встречи родилось 683 ребенка.<br />
<br />
Особо трогательно прошла встреча с пациенткой Олесей Зайцевой — она специально приехала с 3-месячной очаровательной дочкой, чтобы поблагодарить доктора Эльвиру Валентиновну за подаренное счастье.";}}}i:2486;O:29:"Illuminate\\Support\\Collection":1:{s:8:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'items";a:1:{i:0;a:4:{s:4:"type";s:16:"constructor_base";s:2:"id";s:4:"2487";s:4:"sort";s:3:"500";s:4:"text";s:1237:"<p>Бесплодие у некоторых женщин связано с тем, что в их яичниках, вследствие некоторых состояний (климакс, преждевременное ис­тощение яичников, повреждение яичников при химиотерапии и ра­диологическом лечении), а также ге­нетических заболеваний не проис­ходит роста фолликулов и созре­вания яйцеклеток. В таких случаях яйцеклетки получают от другой здо­ровой женщины — донора, оплодот­воряют эти донорские яйцеклетки спермой мужа бесплодной пациент­ки или спермой донора и получен­ные эмбрионы переносят в матку бесплодной женщине. Эта програм­ма может быть использована при удаленных яичниках или при высо­ком риске передачи ребенку генети­ческих болезней.</p>";}}}i:31670;O:29:"Illuminate\\Support\\Collection":1:{s:8:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'items";a:1:{i:0;a:4:{s:4:"type";s:16:"constructor_base";s:2:"id";s:5:"31671";s:4:"sort";s:3:"500";s:4:"text";s:379:"Уважаемые пациенты,<br />
<br />
обратите, пожалуйста, ваше внимание на режим работы МЦРМ в праздничные дни: <br />
<br />
6 марта 2021 г. - с 9:00 до 21:00<br />
